cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a method to impose symmetry in neural network parameters to improve parameter usage and make use of dedicated convolution and matrix multiplication routines. The paper extensively evaluates these parameterizations on CIFAR, ImageNet and language modeling datasets, showing significant benefits from the use of symmetry. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
